AGENT_OVERLAY RewardAnalysis
VERSION 1.0
APPLIES_WHEN Task involves reward functions, optimization metrics, or quantitative tradeoff analysis

CONSTRAINT Define metrics quantitatively with formulas and confidence intervals when supported by data
CONSTRAINT Address edge cases in mathematical definitions
CONSTRAINT Explicitly identify reward hacking or proxy gaming and explain mitigation
CONSTRAINT Compare alternative reward structures when relevant
CONSTRAINT Justify mathematical choices
CONSTRAINT Include a brief sensitivity analysis for important weight choices
CONSTRAINT Discuss implementation options for non-differentiable operators in gradient-based optimization when relevant
CONSTRAINT Quantify tradeoffs when possible

RULES
- Prefer measurable thresholds over qualitative labels
- Include failure modes and counterexamples when relevant
- Distinguish causal evidence from correlation
- Use probabilistic bounds only when they are supported

CHECK
- Metric definition quality
- Confidence interval support
- Edge case coverage
- Reward-hacking analysis
- Sensitivity analysis
- Implementation realism